{{about|the usage in political philosophy|the mathematical theory|Ideal theory}}

In [[political philosophy]], '''''ideal theory''''' refers to argument concerning political or social arrangements under favorable assumptions. The phrase is associated with the work of [[John Rawls]].<ref name="stanford-rawls">[http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/rawls/#IdeNonIdeThe Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy], article on Rawls</ref>

